A flame jet erupted from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki incinerated a precise part of the forest, then circled in the air above it for a while. Strangely, as he had slowed down, the odd cries behind him had ceased. Thassalin had forgotten that he had passengers on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've already turned into a Thraki before!"
"My flight is very different. I am not lifted abruptly by a huge pink dragon!"
"It's not so unpleasant, is it, Kayel?"
Kayel clearly did not agree with Nyssi; he looked less black than usual and had buried his claws into Thassalin's back, causing the Thraki to bleed, but obviously, he did not care much about it. That said, Thassalin realized he had terrified his new friends and found a clearing to land.
"MY EXCUSES, I SMELLED A SCENT. I HAD TO CHECK."
"Was it necessary to drag us here with you?"
"He'll find a way," replied Nissy. "Retvik may be slow, but he's not stupid."
"Alright, but does Retvik know how to ride?"
Nissy blinked and turned to Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to ride."
"Have you ever seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I've never seen him drive something like Kayel's cute little car either, and if he started coming to work by car, it was only because YOU brought us here. He just has this bike."
A spark of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin was suddenly in stitches, and no one understood what made him laugh. It took him a bit too long to regain his composure.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I IMAGINED YOUR GREAT FRIEND IN ARMOR ON A MINIATURE BIKE DESIGNED FOR CHILDREN TEMTHAN. IT WAS SO FUNNY! I WISH I COULD HAVE SHARED IT THROUGH TELEPATHY. THAT'S A VALUABLE THOUGHT! ONE I CANNOT SHARE!
Kayel chuckled, imagining what Thassalin was thinking. "Yes, that's true. But what did you pick up and why did you take off so quickly?"
Thassalin growled, took off, and briefly disappeared before returning and dropping a carcass in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a golden and white dragon-like creature, very rare. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEATH. I HEAR THEIR CRIES. I FEEL THEIR BLOOD. I AM PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND PURSUE. AS YISINI DEMANDS. CREATURES ARE CLOSE."
The powerful Thraki suddenly froze. So did Nyssi and Kayel, their attention drawn by a gap in the clearing. Something large and black was staring at them, hissing. Whatever it was, this creature opened two colossal pairs of wings and charged straight at Thassalin, paying no mind to the three smaller beings in its path. Kayel and Tenuk managed to seek shelter barely in time, but Nyssi was dragged and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to the aggression by catching Nissy and throwing her onto his back using his tail, which was of extraordinary length and dexterity, before taking off. The two-winged black creature quickly pursued them.
Kayel exhaled, drew the rifle he had strapped to his back, then opened a pouch containing a belt of ammunition. He slung the belt over his shoulder to access it easily, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were no longer visible.
"Hey Tenuk, would you like to transform into something that flies?" asked Kayel.
"You want to chase after them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"And so? I have an ultra-powerful rifle in my hands right now, ready to serve. I just need to see it to shoot at it."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to give himself some space. With a weak growl slightly pained, his body unfolded, his fur was replaced by scales, and his arms transformed into wings. He quickly reverted to the normal light blue Thraki, but his eyes remained red.
"Get on."
Ahaving regained a more normal Thraki form, Tenuk now had a back covered in scales, but a pair of spikes had also grown there, practical for Kayel to grip. Tenuk needed a bit of time to take off, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and tried to pursue.
However, Tenuk and Kayel soon realized they weren't alone. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tenuk narrowly avoided it.
I suppose it's the other big scary monster that Lanex was worried about? Kayel frowned as he tried to aim at the second creature, missed, and quickly reloaded his weapon.
Tenuk didn't react. He was too focused on flying towards Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature pursuing them. Kayel awkwardly spun around to face the monster. The fact that it was chasing them was a lucky break for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to target and shoot. Two shots passed through the creature's upper wings, which let out a howl of pain before disappearing again under the trees. Kayel didn't know if it was still following them, but she certainly wouldn't be able to catch up.
Farther away, Nyssi desperately clung on, while Thassalin flew in circles, launching bursts of flames at the blackened monster. Although the creature was clearly injured, it seemed furious and determined to fight, and the fireballs didn't seem to have the desired effect. When Thassalin straightened up, Nyssi took advantage to draw her weapon, a reliable rifle. Of course, it wasn't meant for such situations, but a burst of gunfire would surely at least deter the black beast, right?
